                <div class="div-line"></div>

                     <h2 class="subheading">1.Model Overview & Positioning</h2>

                <h3 class="subheading">Maruti Vitara Brezza</h3>
               
                <p>The Brezza is a stalwart in the sub-4m compact SUV segment. Offered only with a 1.5L petrol engine enhanced with mild-hybrid technology and available in manual, automatic, and CNG configurations, it appeals to buyers seeking fuel economy, reliability, and Maruti's strong service network.</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">Kia Sonet</h3>
                
                <p>Launched in 2020 and facelifted in December 2023, the Sonet offers three engine options (1.2L petrol, 1.0L turbo petrol, 1.5L diesel), multiple gearboxes (MT, iMT/DCT, automatic), and a richer feature set. It delivers a more premium appeal and dynamic drive, targeting urban buyers who value refinement and choice.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">2.Engine & Performance</h2>
                
                <h3 class="subheading">Maruti Brezza</h3>
                
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Engine:</span> 1,462cc K-Series DualJet Dual-VVT petrol</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Power:</span> ~101.6 bhp 102 PS@6,000 rpm</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Torque:</span> ~137 Nm@4,400 rpm</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Transmission:</span> 5-speed MT, 6-speed automatic (torque converter)</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Mild-hybrid (SHVS)</span> standard on petrol variants; CNG version also available</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">Kia Sonet</h3>
            
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">1.2L NA petrol (1,197cc):</span> ~82 PS; torque ~115 Nm; paired with 5-speed MT</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">1.0L turbo GDi petrol:</span> ~120 PS, 172 Nm; available with iMT, DCT, or MT</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">1.5L diesel CRDi:</span> 85 kW (~115 PS) and 250 Nm; MT, iMT, or 6-speed torque converter</li>
                </ul>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Takeaway:</span> Brezza's NA engine with mild-hybrid tech delivers smooth, linear power and enhanced mileage. Sonet offers greater flexibility: the turbo petrol relishes mid-range punch, while the diesel delivers strong torque, especially at low revs.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">3.Fuel Efficiency (ARAI)</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Brezza Petrol MT/AT:</span> 17.38-19.9 kmpl</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Brezza Petrol AT:</span> ~19.8 kmpl</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Brezza CNG MT:</span> 25.51 km/kg</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Sonet 1.2L petrol:</span> ~19 kmpl</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Sonet 1.0L turbo petrol:</span> ~18.4 kmpl</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Sonet Diesel:</span> ~24.1 kmpl</li>
                </ul>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Takeaway:</span> Brezza leads in pure petrol efficiency thanks to its mild-hybrid and CNG offering. Sonet's diesel closely trails, while turbo petrol offers mid-tier mileage.</p>

