                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Takeaway:</span> The Brezza and Sonet share external dimensions, but Sonet offers more boot space, while Brezza provides slightly lower ground clearance.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">5.Safety & Ratings</h2>
                
                <h3 class="subheading">Maruti Brezza</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Equipped with 6 airbags, ESP, ABS with EBD, hill-hold assist, Suzuki-TECT body</li>
                    <li>No recent GNCAP rating for the current model</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">Kia Sonet</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Standard with 6 airbags, ESC, VSM, HAC, BVM blind-spot monitor, 360° camera, parking sensors</li>
                    <li>Kia globally scores well in crash ratings, though no direct Indian GNCAP score for facelift yet</li>
                </ul>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Takeaway:</span> Both cars come well-equipped with safety tech. Sonet edges ahead with additional systems like BVM and 360° camera.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">6.Features & Comfort</h2>
                
                <h3 class="subheading">Maruti Brezza</h3>
              
                <ul>
                    <li>9″ SmartPlay Pro+ infotainment with wireless Android Auto/Apple CarPlay</li>
                    <li>Heads-up display, wireless charger, sunroof, rear AC vents, 360° camera (on higher trims)</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">Kia Sonet</h3>
               
                <ul>
                    <li>8″/10.67″ touchscreen with wired or wireless Android Auto/Apple CarPlay</li>
                    <li>Connected UVO tech, sunroof, ventilated seats, air purifier, Bose 7-speaker system (on top trims), 360° camera</li>
                </ul>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Takeaway:</span> Sonet brings more high-end tech and premium audio in top trims, while Brezza focuses on essential and useful convenience features.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">7.Ride & Handling</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Brezza:</span> MacPherson front & torsion beam rear; ride tuned for compliance on Indian roads. Mild-hybrid assists seamless acceleration</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Sonet:</span> Likely similar suspension setup; slightly firmer ride for sporty handling. Turbo petrol and diesel feel lively, with DCT delivering smooth performance</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
